Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?feat:=20User=20Management=20=E2=80=94=20class/s?=
 =?UTF-8?q?ection,=20password=20column,=20direct=20export,=20staff=20in=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?create-missing?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Four enhancements to the User Login Management page:

1. "Create Missing Logins" now also creates accounts for any Staff
   record with user_id = NULL (defensive — Staff is normally created
   with a User, but imports / older data sometimes lack one). All new
   logins use the universal default password 'password'. Returned
   credentials now include class_name + section_name when applicable
   (parents → first child's class/section; students → own).

2. Each row in the table now shows the password as 'password' with a
   small 'default' hint. (Hashed passwords can't be recovered, but
   since every reset / create defaults to 'password', this matches
   reality until the user changes it on first login.)

3. Class · Section appears under the name for students and parents,
   replacing the phone/email line for those roles. The eager-loads
   pull through student.currentAcademicHistory and
   studentParent.students.currentAcademicHistory so this is one query.

4. New "Excel" / "PDF" buttons next to "Create Missing Logins" do a
   direct export of the currently-filtered list — no bulk-reset
   needed. New endpoint: GET /school/users/export-list?format=… that
   honours the same filters as index() (search, user_type, status,
   class_id, section_id). Uses the same UserCredentialsExport class
   and exports/user-credentials.blade.php — both updated to add Class
   and Section columns.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
